 Way sheds light on an ambiguous period in the histories of architecture, medicine, and women, revealing it to be a time of turmoil, not of progress and reform as is often assumed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArchitecture and womenzEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 0aArchitecture, DomesticxHealth aspectszEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 0aArchitecture, DomesticxSocial aspectszEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 0aArchitecture, VictorianzEngland. 0aHousing and healthzEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356586940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773565869423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773565869/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles